names.alias: Class C core vacuole/endosome tethering complex.

attributeList.attribute: Multisubunit tethering complex involved in early endosomal fusions by cross-linking two membranes, and facilitating the formation of a SNARE complex during fusion. Cooperates with Rab GTPases to capture vesicles and trap them prior to the action of SNAREs. Catalyses either vacuole fission into sub-compartments or vacuole-endosome fusion, or both, by interacting with the Rab GTPase VPS21 (P36017) to promote tethering and fusion of RAB5/VPS21-positive membranes.
